    "causal_summary": "The 029 model benchmark caught /memory:search confidently citing an off-corpus term, kubernetes scored good at 0.78 on a semantically unrelated doc, but the eval harness cannot reproduce it. All six existing ground-truth hard-negatives are in-corpus decoys with a real relevance-3 target, so no sample tests the absent-term case, and the falseGoodOnHardNegatives metric that would measure it already ships yet sits dormant with no driver and no CI gate. This phase adds an off_corpus class with absent terms and zero relevance rows, pins kubernetes as a permanent regression anchor, wires the dormant metric behind a false-confirm driver, and gates the measured rate behind a default-off threshold with a grandfather report mode, turning the one-off manual benchmark into a permanent guard without moving the verdict.",
